---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'AZFFL — Arizona Female Foot Lover | azffl.me';
const description =
  'AZFFL — Arizona Female Foot Lover. A poetic meditation on the quiet worship of the feminine sole in the desert Southwest.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <SEO title={title} description={description} pathname="/" />
  <StructuredData
    schema={{
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@graph': [
        {
          '@type': 'WebSite',
          name: 'AZFFL',
          alternateName: 'Arizona Female Foot Lover',
          description: description,
          url: 'https://azffl.me',
        },
      ],
    }}
  />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-2 mb-6 px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#EDE4D8] bg-white/60">
      <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[#9F5A3C] rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
      <span class="text-xs tracking-[2px] text-[#6B5F57] font-medium">EST. 2026 • PHOENIX, ARIZONA</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="heading-serif text-[4.25rem] md:text-[5.5rem] leading-[0.95] tracking-tighter text-balance mb-4">
      Arizona Female<br />Foot Lover
    </h1>

    <p class="max-w-md mx-auto text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#6B5F57] tracking-tight font-light">
      The longing that arrives at the feet.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 text-[#9F5A3C]">
        <div class="h-px w-8 bg-[#D4C9B8]"></div>
        <span class="elegant-symbol text-xl">✦</span>
        <div class="h-px w-8 bg-[#D4C9B8]"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose mx-auto text-[#6B5F57] text-[15px]">
      A meditation on the feminine foot in the sun-drenched landscapes of the American Southwest —
      where heat, dust, and light transform the sole into a landscape of quiet reverence.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-24">

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <div class="max-w-[68ch] mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.85] text-xl text-[#3F342E]">
        AZFFL is not a collection of images or a catalog of desire. It is a quiet acknowledgment
        of a particular form of attention — the kind that notices the way a foot rests against
        cool tile after a long desert walk, the subtle flex of an arch beneath a leather sandal strap,
        or the faint imprint left in red Arizona dust.
      </p>

      <p class="text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.85] mt-6">
        In a state defined by vast skies and relentless sun, the foot becomes something more than
        anatomy. It becomes a record of movement, a vessel of sensation, and for some, an object
        of profound aesthetic and sensual appreciation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol text-lg">✦ ✦ ✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Definition -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="heading-serif text-4xl tracking-tighter mb-6 text-center">What is AZFFL?</h2>

      <div class="max-w-[68ch] mx-auto space-y-6 text-[15.5px]">
        <p>
          <span class="font-medium text-[#9F5A3C]">Arizona Female Foot Lover</span> describes a specific
          sensibility: an appreciation for the elegant architecture of the feminine foot,
          heightened and contextualized by the unique environment of the Sonoran Desert and
          the broader Southwest.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is the recognition that in Arizona's particular light — harsh yet clarifying —
          every curve, every line, every subtle variation in skin tone and texture tells a story.
          The foot here is not hidden. It is presented, adorned, and observed in ways that
          feel both ancient and entirely contemporary.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol">✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Meditations -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="heading-serif text-4xl tracking-tighter mb-8 text-center">Meditations on the Sole</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <!-- Meditation 1 -->
        <div class="meditation-card bg-white border border-[#EDE4D8] rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-[0_10px_15px_-3px_rgb(0_0_0_/_0.03)]">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-[#9F5A3C] text-lg">☀</span>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight">The Desert Touch</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149] text-[14.5px]">
            Arizona's climate creates a unique dialogue between skin and environment.
            The contrast between scorching pavement and the sudden coolness of shaded
            stone or air-conditioned interiors heightens every sensation. The foot
            becomes acutely aware of texture, temperature, and pressure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Meditation 2 -->
        <div class="meditation-card bg-white border border-[#EDE4D8] rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-[0_10px_15px_-3px_rgb(0_0_0_/_0.03)]">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-[#9F5A3C] text-lg">👁</span>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight">The Philosophy of Presentation</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149] text-[14.5px]">
            A pedicure in the desert is not mere grooming — it is a ritual of
            self-regard. The choice of color, the shape of the nail, the way light
            catches the instep: these are quiet declarations. To notice them is to
            participate in a private language of care and beauty.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Meditation 3 -->
        <div class="meditation-card bg-white border border-[#EDE4D8] rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-[0_10px_15px_-3px_rgb(0_0_0_/_0.03)]">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-[#9F5A3C] text-lg">♡</span>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight">The Intimacy of Observation</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149] text-[14.5px]">
            There is a particular vulnerability in the foot. Unlike the face or hands,
            it is rarely performed for an audience. When it is offered — bare on a
            pool deck, resting on a car dashboard during a drive through the valley,
            or slipping from a sandal at day's end — the act carries weight.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol">✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Taxonomy -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="heading-serif text-4xl tracking-tighter mb-3 text-center">A Taxonomy of the Sole</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-[#6B5F57] mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto">Archetypes of reverence observed in the Arizona light</p>

      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-8">
        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">The High Arch Offering</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">The elegant upward curve that seems to present itself, creating negative space that invites the eye and suggests both strength and delicacy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">Sandal Season Surrender</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">The moment leather straps meet sun-warmed skin. The visible contrast between bound and unbound, the slight indentations left by straps after hours of wear.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">Post-Hike Sole</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">Dust-kissed and alive. The foot that has met red rock, desert trail, and the surprising coolness of shaded canyon floors. A map of the day's journey.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">The Painted Canvas</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">Toes as individual expressions. A deep burgundy, a soft sage, a bold turquoise — each choice a small act of curation against the neutral desert palette.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">Poolside Reverie</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">Feet resting at the edge of turquoise water, skin cooled by evaporation, the faint scent of sunscreen and chlorine mixing with natural skin warmth.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="taxonomy-item">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight mb-1">The Silent Step</h4>
          <p class="text-[#5C5149]">The almost imperceptible movement across cool kitchen tile at dawn or across sun-baked concrete at dusk. Presence announced through pressure and release alone.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol">✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Biology & Art -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="heading-serif text-4xl tracking-tighter mb-6 text-center">The Biology of Reverence</h2>

      <div class="max-w-[68ch] mx-auto space-y-6 text-[15px]">
        <p>
          The human foot contains approximately <span class="font-medium">200,000 nerve endings</span> —
          more per square centimeter than nearly any other region of the body except the hands and lips.
          This dense network of sensory receptors makes the foot not merely a structure for locomotion,
          but a profound instrument of perception.
        </p>

        <p>
          In the desert, where temperature swings can exceed 40 degrees between day and night,
          these nerve endings become exquisitely attuned. The difference between the heat of
          a car's floorboard and the relief of a shaded patio is registered with remarkable clarity.
        </p>

        <p>
          There is also the matter of proportion and line. The female foot, with its typically
          higher arch and more pronounced taper toward the toes, creates visual rhythms that
          many find inherently pleasing — the same aesthetic principles that govern classical
          sculpture and architecture.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol">✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Arizona Context -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="heading-serif text-4xl tracking-tighter mb-6 text-center">Arizona as Canvas</h2>

      <div class="max-w-[68ch] mx-auto">
        <p class="text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.85]">
          This particular form of appreciation is inseparable from place. The red-orange dust
          of Sedona that clings to the skin. The way late afternoon light in the Valley of the Sun
          turns everything golden, including the subtle contours of a bare instep. The ritual of
          removing shoes after a hike on South Mountain or Camelback, soles meeting cool tile
          or soft rug.
        </p>

        <p class="text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.85] mt-5">
          In Arizona, feet are not always concealed by heavy boots or thick socks. The climate
          encourages openness — sandals, slides, bare feet on pool decks and yoga mats. This
          openness creates opportunities for observation that feel natural rather than staged.
          The desert itself seems to collaborate in the revelation.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 p-6 border-l-2 border-[#9F5A3C] bg-[#F4EDE4]">
          <p class="italic text-[#5C5149]">
            "We fall in love with the landscape of the body long before we understand
            what is happening in the mind — the eye has already decided."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">
      <span class="elegant-symbol text-lg">✦ ✦ ✦</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <div class="text-center max-w-xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xl text-[#3F342E] leading-relaxed">
        To love the foot in Arizona is to love the way light moves across skin,
        the way dust settles and is brushed away, the way a single step can carry
        both the weight of the day and the promise of evening.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-[#6B5F57]">
        It is a quiet practice. One that requires no explanation to those who feel it,
        and no defense to those who do not.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <div class="inline-block px-8 py-3 border border-[#D4C9B8] rounded-full">
          <span class="text-sm tracking-[2px] text-[#9F5A3C] font-medium">AZFFL.ME</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8A7666]">
        the quiet worship of the sole
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

</Layout>
